  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GoActiveForGirls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Northern Ghana, as soon as a girl gets married, she often has to stop school and her husband takes control. More often than not, she becomes the (too-)young mother of a child born into a new generation, destined to grow up in poverty. Alongside poverty, the taboo associated with premarital sex is a major driver of the high number of child marriages. To sustainably improve  Girls&apos; Health, Education and rights, enhanced efforts are needed to build their capacity to make safe choices.</narrative>
  </description>
